OL,3,CLocal Elections 2026: The results on
OL,4,Cthe Isle of Wight as the island decides
OL,6,FThe Isle of Wight is a unitary
OL,7,Fauthority which means a single
OL,8,Fgovernment body based in Newport runs
OL,9,Fall local services within its area,
OL,10,Fincluding education, housing,
OL,11,Fplanning, social care, and waste
OL,12,Fmanagement.
OL,14,FVoters will be some of the oldest in
OL,15,Fthe UK as the population on the island
OL,16,Fhas a greater proportion of people
OL,17,Faged over 50, and a lower proportion
OL,18,Fof working aged people aged 20 to 44
OL,19,Fyears.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
