OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1778332261
OL,3,CLocal Elections 2026: The results on
OL,4,Cthe Isle of Wight as the island decides
OL,6,FThe island is also the 83rd most
OL,7,Fdeprived authority in England
OL,8,Faccording to the Index of Multiple
OL,9,FDeprivation (IMD) 2025.
OL,11,FHowever, Ryde and Ventnor fall within
OL,12,Fthe most deprived areas in the country.
OL,14,FThe population of the Isle of Wight in
OL,15,F2024 is estimated to be around 141,00
OL,16,Fpeople.
OL,18,FThe Island's population is expected to
OL,19,Fincrease by 3.5% between 2024 to 2031.
OL,20,FThis equates to an increase of almost
OL,21,F5,000 people.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
