OL,3,CLocal Elections 2026: The results on
OL,4,Cthe Isle of Wight as the island decides
OL,6,FAny party that takes control will have
OL,7,Fto manage ever-increasing demands of
OL,8,Fsocial care, and navigate local
OL,9,Fgovernment reorganisation.
OL,11,FThe Isle of Wight Council will survive
OL,12,Fcouncil changes, but is due to fall
OL,13,Funder the new Hampshire and the Solent
OL,14,Fmayoral authority.
OL,16,FFor the island, this means these
OL,17,Felections will choose who oversees a
OL,18,Fperiod of change, as the make-up of
OL,19,Fcouncils on the mainland in Hampshire
OL,20,Fchanges.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/6
